&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-size : small"&gt;&lt;span style="font-size : small"&gt;&lt;em&gt;"Breath is the movement of Spirit in the body... &lt;br /&gt;

There is no single more powerful way to further &lt;br /&gt;

your well-being than breathwork."&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="font-size : medium"&gt;&lt;span style="font-size : medium"&gt;&lt;span style="font-size : small"&gt;~ Andrew Weil, M.D.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;br /&gt;

&lt;span&gt;SunDo Mountain Taoism is pleased to offer the 2012-13 Taoist Yoga Training Program, Grounding &amp;amp; Centering Level I, for students or instructors. Our training program is dedicated to creating practitioners who have a strong sense of self-realization and wholeness.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="font-size : small"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Free Information Sessions&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt; &lt;br /&gt;

&lt;span style="font-size : small"&gt;Thursday February 9 from 7-9 pm&lt;/span&gt; &lt;br /&gt;

&lt;span style="font-size : small"&gt;Saturday February 11 from 3-5 pm&lt;/span&gt; &lt;br /&gt;

&lt;span style="font-size : small"&gt;Sunday February 26 from 3-5 pm&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-size : small"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;To register: email &lt;a href="mailto:questions@sundo.org"&gt;questions@sundo.org&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-size : small"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Classes start March 1, 2012 &lt;br /&gt;

&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-size : small"&gt;&lt;span style="font-size : small"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="font-size : small"&gt;&lt;span style="font-size : medium"&gt;&lt;span style="font-size : medium"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style="font-size : small"&gt;Four Phases of Level I Training Program &lt;br /&gt;

&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-size : small"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="font-size : small"&gt;&lt;span style="font-size : medium"&gt;&lt;span style="font-size : medium"&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-size : large"&gt;1 -&lt;/span&gt; &lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style="font-size : small"&gt;&lt;span style="font-size : small"&gt;Deepening the Breath&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt; &lt;span style="font-size : x-small"&gt;10 classes&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-size : small"&gt;In this first phase, the focus is on feeling relaxed and calm enough to deepen the breath using the Level I Taoist breathwork.&amp;nbsp; This balanced breathing will eventually lead to the ability to deepen the breath even more and cultivate Qi during forthcoming practice levels.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-size : small"&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-size : small"&gt;2 - &lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style="font-size : small"&gt;&lt;span style="font-size : small"&gt;Connecting to the Energetic Core&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;span style="font-size : small"&gt;&lt;span style="font-size : x-small"&gt;30 classes&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="font-size : small"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="font-size : small"&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt; &lt;br /&gt;
 &lt;br /&gt;
  &lt;br /&gt;
 &lt;br /&gt;
 
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-size : small"&gt;Using the breath to guide visualization, a student begins to experience the grounding quality of the lower abdomen&amp;rsquo;s core energy center, the dan-tien.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
 &lt;br /&gt;
 &lt;br /&gt;
 
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-size : large"&gt;3 -&lt;/span&gt; &lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style="font-size : small"&gt;&lt;span style="font-size : small"&gt;Developing the Spiral Breath&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt; &lt;span style="font-size : x-small"&gt;30 classes&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-size : small"&gt;Because energy tends to move, grow and balance itself as a spiral, in this phase, a student is given a specific visualization on which to concentrate while practicing Level I breathing.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-size : small"&gt;&lt;span style="font-size : large"&gt;&lt;span style="font-size : large"&gt;4 -&lt;/span&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style="font-size : small"&gt;&lt;span style="font-size : small"&gt;Balancing the Five Element Energies&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="font-size : x-small"&gt;30 classes&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;span style="font-size : small"&gt;&lt;span style="font-size : small"&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt; &lt;br /&gt;
 &lt;br /&gt;
  
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-size : small"&gt;The five elements correspond to the essential qualities of Qi energy as it exists in the universe. Once proper breathing patterns and visualizations are established, students will start to focus on the energetic expression of each posture that balances a certain elemental energy.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
